description:
Comment: The exposition was shortened at some places and clarified at others.
  The proof of Theorem 5.8 had a slight gap which we fixed (without consequence
  for the result)

  We prove that probability $P_n$ that $n\times n$ random matrix with uniform
distributed $\pm 1$ entries is singular satisfies asymptotic inequality $P_n =
2^{-n+o(n)}
